"title":{
"__html":"Infective Endocarditis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"b92cb6",
"children":[
"Infective Endocarditis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s29_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Prevention"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"c53b76",
"children":[
"Prevention"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"c47036",
"children":[
"Provide prophylaxis for ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"infective endocarditis",
"children":[
"IE"
]
},
" only in patients with the highest risk, including those with:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c538da",
"children":[
"prosthetic cardiac valve"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0641d1",
"children":[
"history of IE"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"7069c3",
"children":[
"unrepaired cyanotic congenital heart disease"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"a93753",
"children":[
"repaired congenital heart defect with prosthesis or shunt (≤6 months postprocedure) or residual defect"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"04fb5b",
"children":[
"valvulopathy following cardiac transplantation"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"703369",
"children":[
"prosthetic material used for cardiac valve repair (annuloplasty rings and chords)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"76d286",
"children":[
"Antibiotic prophylaxis is reasonable in patients at high risk for IE before dental procedures that involve mucosal bleeding."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e96291",
"children":[
"Antibiotic prophylaxis is not recommended in patients at high risk for IE undergoing nondental procedures (e.g., ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"transesophageal echocardiography",
"children":[
"TEE"
]
},
","
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"esophagogastroduodenoscopy",
"children":[
"EGD"
]
},
","
]
},
" colonoscopy, or cystoscopy) in the absence of active infection."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"ab04e5",
"children":[
"Most patients requiring prophylaxis will be undergoing dental procedures, and the indicated antibiotic is oral amoxicillin 30 to 60 minutes before the procedure. If the patient is allergic to penicillin, use cephalexin, azithromycin, clarithromycin, or clindamycin."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s29_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"b8b43a",
"children":[
"Fever, malaise, and fatigue are sensitive but nonspecific symptoms associated with IE. Suggestive physical examination findings include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f4667c",
"children":[
"new cardiac murmur"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"4d8e91",
"children":[
"new-onset ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"heart failure",
"children":[
"HF"
]
}
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"27c524",
"children":[
"conduction abnormalities on ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"electrocardiogram",
"children":[
"ECG"
]
},
" (suggests perivalvular abscess)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"6d29a8",
"children":[
"petechiae, splinter hemorrhages"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"bddf60",
"children":[
"Osler nodes (violaceous, circumscribed, painful nodules found in the pulp of the fingers and toes)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"d9d9e9",
"children":[
"Janeway lesions (painless, erythematous, macular lesions found on the soles and palms)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c39156",
"children":[
"Roth spots (hemorrhagic lesions of the retina)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0626da",
"children":[
"leukocytosis, anemia, and hematuria"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"037035",
"children":[
"focal neurologic signs (septic emboli)"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"16629c",
"children":[
"multiple bilateral small nodules on chest x-ray (septic emboli)"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"2",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_cv_f26"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"3",
