],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"a909ff",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"transthoracic echocardiography",
"children":[
"TTE"
]
},
" is the initial imaging test in all patients."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"cddba8",
"children":[
"TEE is recommended in the following situations:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"fa5990",
"children":[
"all patients with known or suspected IE and nondiagnostic TTE"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"0b3d5c",
"children":[
"when complications have developed or are clinically suspected"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"c89edc",
"children":[
"when intracardiac device leads are present"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"abd9bb",
"children":[
"Diagnose endocarditis in patients with two major Duke criteria, one major and three minor criteria, five minor criteria, or pathologic confirmation."
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"1",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_cv_s29_inline_t1"
],
"forceOpen":true
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"59eb5d",
"children":[
"Don't give antimicrobial prophylaxis to patients with ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"mitral valve prolapse",
"children":[
"MVP"
]
},
" or other low-risk valvular abnormalities."
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"3e27c5",
"children":[
"Look for colon cancer in patients with ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Streptococcus bovis"
]
},
" or ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Clostridium septicum"
]
},
" endocarditis."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"inline-wrap",
"wrapId":"5",
"contentIds":[
"mk19_bb_cv_f29"
],
"forceOpen":true
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_cv_s29_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"245545",
"children":[
"Indications for surgery include:"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"97d1d5",
"children":[
"valvular dysfunction and acute HF"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"9f9f42",
"children":[
"left-sided IE caused by ",
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Staphylococcus aureus"
]
},
", fungal infection, or highly resistant organisms"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"f43c59",
"children":[
"heart block"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ac2e17",
"children":[
"annular or aortic abscess"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"b3cfee",
"children":[
"recurrent systemic embolization on antibiotic therapy"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"55bef9",
"children":[
"prosthetic valve endocarditis with relapsing infection or dehiscence"
]
},
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"511cff",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"i",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"S. aureus"
]
},
" prosthetic valve endocarditis"
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"9a1105",
"children":[
"Patients with suspected IE and good cardiovascular function do not require empiric treatment before culture results. In decompensated patients, start empiric antibiotics immediately after blood cultures are obtained."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"818332",
"children":[
"Narrow antibiotic selection after susceptibilities are known. Continue treatment for 4 to 6 weeks except in uncomplicated right-sided native valve endocarditis caused by ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"methicillin-sensitive Staphylococcus aureus",
"children":[
"MSSA"
]
},
","
]
},
" which can be treated for 2 weeks with a combination of nafcillin, oxacillin, or flucloxacillin."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"5c1034",
"children":[
"Oral antibiotics are not recommended for treatment of IE."
]
},
" "
]
}
]
}
]
},
